source: The private:// file system is not configured so the exported files will be stored in the public:// files directory. Click here for instructions on configuring the private files in the settings.php file.
Allow anonymous users to download this file
Change the way rows are processed.
Check this if you want to configure a custom redirect path.
Check this if you want to download the file immediately after it is created. Does NOT work for JSON data exports.
Check this if you want to include query string parameters on redirect.
Check this if you want to store the export files in the public:// files directory instead of the private:// files directory.
Choose the facet source used to alter data export. This should be the display that this data export is attached to.
Configurable row output for data exports.
Could not write to temporary output file for result export (@file). Check permissions.
Determines the encoding used for CSV cell values.
Enter custom path to redirect user after batch finishes.
Export complete. Download the file here.
Export complete. Download the file here if file is not automatically downloaded.
Export failed. Make sure the private file system is configured and check the error log.
Export the view results to a file. Can handle very large result sets.
Exports data in sequences. Should be used when large amount of data is exported (> 2000 rows).
Exports under one request. Best fit for small exports.
Include query string parameters on redirect
Indicates the character used for escaping. Defaults to a backslash (\\).
Indicates the character used for field enclosure. Defaults to a double quote (").
Indicates the character used to delimit fields. Defaults to a comma (,). For tab-separation use \\t characters.
Plugin to export views data into various file formats.
Select the display to redirect to after batch finishes. If None is selected the user will be redirected to the front page.
Skips the symfony data normalize method when rendering data export to increase performance on large datasets. (Only use when not exporting nested data)
Store file in public files directory
Strips HTML tags from CSV cell values.
The data export icon will be available only to the selected displays.
The filename that will be suggested to the browser for downloading purposes. You may include replacement patterns from the list below.
The maximum amount of rows to export.
The maximum amount of rows to export. 0 means unlimited.
The number of rows to process under a request.
Trims whitespace from beginning and end of CSV cell values.
